Moy, King  | Engineering Alumni | University of Illinois at Chicago                     It all starts with a single spark         Skip to the content of this page ,  the main menu , the site search form , the site home page .        UIC Logo        Engineering Alumni     Search the site     Toggle Menu      Search                  UIC Logo          Engineering Alumni      Engineering Alumni   Main Menu    News    Expand News menu           Dean's List    RISE Magazine         Events    Expand Events menu           Upcoming Events         Get Involved    Expand Get Involved menu           Join us on LinkedIn    Become a Mentor    Volunteer    Engineer your own involvement    Honor a Professor         Awards    Expand Awards menu           2019 Alumni Award Honorees    2018 Alumni Award Honorees    2017 Alumni Award Honorees         Give    Contact     Eyebrow menu    College of Engineering    Engineering Career Center    UIC menu    UIC.edu    Campus Map       Search                           King  Moy  Champion's Award   Electrical and Computer Engineering               About   King Moy is an engineer who pushes for innovation during product development while adding realism to final concepts delivered to his clients.He started his career at HLB, honing his skills at designing industrial, medical, and consumer electronics while working with multi-disciplinary teams.Here he mastered human-centered design based approaches to engineering while working with ethnographic and sensor based research teams; collaborations which resulted in the development of technology assessment studies to identify solutions to design problems or roadmaps for innovation, now known as smart data.Following HLB, King applied his skills at RTC Industries, where he managed multi-national and multi-disciplinary teams in the development of leading edge interactive retail technology from concept to manufacturing and deployment.Currently, King is the Electrical Engineering Group Leader at Inventus Power where his team is designing novel energy storage solutions for commercial, medical and military customers around the world. King holds an MS in Electrical and Computer Engineering and a BS in Computer Engineering from UIC.While successfully delivering numerous products to market over the years, he has received several patents and awards.He actively mentorsengineers and students, encouraging them to continue learning while offering career guidance at UIC and at Northwestern where he serves as a Segal Design Institute Affiliate.Additionally, he continues to make connections between academia and industry bypromoting joint ventures between the two.                    UIC Logo        Engineering Alumni       Contact   851 S. Morgan - SEO Rm. 811  Phone: 3129969422  MWilli60@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    Facebook            UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI Health  Veterans Affairs        Powered by Red 2.38.0  Â© 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois |  Privacy Statement    Campuses   University of Illinois System  Urbana-Champaign  Springfield      Cookie Settings                 